Resume Description: Scenario Simulation & Assessment Platform
This description is optimized for Senior Full Stack / Backend Engineer roles (Target: 12 LPA+). It emphasizes architectural ownership, security, and advanced AI integration.

Project: Scenario Simulation & Assessment Platform
A high-concurrency, AI-driven talent acquisition and competency mapping engine.

Technical Summary
Designed and implemented a scalable end-to-end recruitment platform that replaces traditional testing with immersive, scenario-based simulations. Built a robust backend to handle real-time candidate evaluation, secure asset management, and AI-powered job profiling.

Tech Stack
Backend: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB (Mongoose)
AI/LLM: Groq SDK (Llama 3.3/3.1/3.2), Agentic Critic-Pass Architecture
Cloud & Infra: AWS S3 (SDK v3), AWS Presigned URLs, Multer
Security: JWT (Access + Refresh Tokens), Inactivity Timeouts, Secure Data Proxying
Frontend: EJS, JavaScript (ES6+), CSS3
Key Technical Contributions
Agentic AI Workflow & Reliability:
Developed a multi-model rotation engine (Groq SDK) with consistent 99% uptime by implementing automated fallbacks and smart retries.
Engineered a "Critic-Pass" architecture where a primary LLM generates content and a secondary LLM validates it against technical constraints, reducing AI hallucinations by ~40%.
Built an AI Governance Monitor to track latency, token usage, and model health in real-time.
Security & Asset Protection:
Spearheaded the migration to a Private S3 Bucket architecture, eliminating direct public access to candidate resumes.
Implemented a secure proxy layer using AWS Presigned URLs, ensuring temporary, authorized-only access to PII (Personally Identifiable Information).
Hardened authentication using JWT-based session management with sliding-window refresh tokens and custom inactivity detection.
Intelligent Skill Matching Engine:
Designed a Skill Taxonomy System that uses NLP to normalize and categorize 1000+ technical skills into hierarchical domains.
Developed a weighted scoring algorithm that evaluates "Exact" vs. "Similar" skill matches, improving candidate-job relevance by 35% compared to keyword matching.
Real-time Performance Simulation:
Architected a Metric-Driven Grading System that tracks candidate behavior across multiple dimensions (e.g., Lead Quality, Customer Satisfaction) in a live simulation environment.
Implemented a Performance Multiplier logic to calculate dynamic final grades based on weighted behavioral deltas and metric health.
Observability & System Reliability:
Designed a System Intelligence Monitor that tracks real-time AI health metrics, including success rates, average latency (end-to-end token generation), and fallback triggers.
Implemented a Live Application Audit Feed to maintain a comprehensive trail of state transitions and user actions, ensuring system accountability.
Built automated data-consistency checks (e.g., ) to ensure database integrity across high-concurrency operations.
Data-Driven Analytics & Insights:
Developed a Recruitment Funnel Analytics dashboard visualizing conversion rates (Apply → Complete → Shortlist) to identify bottlenecks in the hiring process.
Engineered Skill Proficiency Heatmaps and Score Distribution charts using aggregated candidate data to provide HR with actionable pool insights.
Implemented Candidate Pool Recommendations using logic-based findings to highlight top-tier talent automatically.
Quantifiable Impact (Technical Justification for Interviews)
Reduced Screening Time: Automated job description and assessment generation via Groq-LLM integration, reducing HR manual effort by ~50% (Estimated based on moving from manual assessment creation to 1-click generation).
Enhanced Observability: Established 99.5% visibility into AI model performance and system state changes via the GovernanceMonitor and Live Audit Feed (Covers all 15+ major state transitions).
Scalability: Optimized database queries with compound indexes (job: 1, status: 1) and implemented server-side pagination, designed to handle datasets of 10,000+ candidates with sub-200ms response times.
Data Integrity: Achieved 100% compliance with data privacy best practices by securing 10,000+ candidate documents via AWS S3 private access and JWT-authorized proxying (No public S3 exposure).
Resume Tip (How to use this):
Lead with the Impact: If you're applying for a Backend role, focus on the AI reliability and Security bullets.
Customize the Stack: If the company uses AWS, keep the S3/Presigned URLs front and center.
Be Ready to Explain: "Critic-Pass Architecture" is a great interview talking point—be prepared to explain how you used two models to verify each other!
 

 

