Several Indian product, fintech, and health-tech companies offer entry-level Software Development Engineer (SDE1), Graduate Trainee, or Associate roles with salaries exceeding ₹8 LPA. Many of these companies rely on Node.js for their backend or full-stack operations. [1, 2, 3]

1. Fintech Industry

Fintech is currently one of the highest-paying sectors for freshers in India, with entry-level salaries often starting at ₹12–15 LPA.

Razorpay: Offers SDE1 roles starting around ₹15 LPA. They use a modern stack that includes Node.js and Go.
Groww: Actively hires for SDE1 roles (Full Stack/Backend) with starting packages of ₹14–22 LPA.
PhonePe: One of the top paymasters, with entry-level CTCs frequently exceeding ₹18–25 LPA.
Paytm: Offers Software Engineer roles for freshers (0–1 years) with salaries typically in the ₹10–18 LPA range.
Pine Labs: Known for hiring freshers with packages starting around ₹12 LPA.
Slice: A fast-growing fintech that pays SDE1s approximately ₹14–22 LPA. [1, 4, 5]
2. Health-Tech Industry

Health-tech startups have significantly increased their compensation to compete for top engineering talent.

Practo: Offers SDE1 positions with a salary range of ₹11–18 LPA.
SigTuple: A niche AI-health company that hires Software Engineer interns and associates.
Nova Benefits: Known to hire SDE Interns with a focus on conversion to full-time roles.
ADDV HealthTech Solutions: Often has requirements for Node.js developers. [1, 6, 7, 8]
3. Product-Based Companies (E-commerce & SaaS)

These companies frequently hire "Node-based" or "Full-stack" developers for their core products. [9]

CloudSEK: As discussed, they offer ₹11–15 LPA for SDE1 roles and are active in the cybersecurity product space.
Meesho: Known for aggressive hiring of SDE1s with packages ranging from ₹12–20 LPA.
Lenskart: Offers entry-level engineering roles starting at ₹11–18 LPA.
