soo can u clerly tell me the techstack.. th... by Shaik Bisma Alisha
Wednesday 8:35 PM
Shaik Bisma Alisha

soo can u clerly tell me the techstack..

the ui (example) and how it must work

2:06 PM

 

Claude responded: Sure!
Sure! Here's a clear breakdown:

Tech Stack
Backend: Python 3.10+ with Flask (web framework)

ML Libraries: XGBoost (quantile regression), scikit-learn (Linear Regression, Random Forest, train_test_split), Pandas (data cleaning), NumPy (numerical ops)

Frontend: Plain HTML + CSS + JavaScript (no React, no frameworks — just one index.html file with Canvas-based charts)

Data: CSV file (150K rows of retail sales data)

Optional: Jupyter Notebook (for interactive analysis), boto3 (AWS SageMaker deployment), Matplotlib/Seaborn (chart generation in Python)

How It Works
 

Plain Text


User opens browser (localhost:5000)        │        ▼   Flask serves index.html        │        ▼   User clicks "Run Forecast"        │        ▼   JavaScript sends POST to /api/forecast        │        ▼   Flask receives request        │        ▼   Python runs XGBoost quantile models (Q10, Q50, Q90)   + Holt-Winters + Linear Trend   → combines them 60/20/20        │        ▼   Flask returns JSON with predictions + metrics        │        ▼   JavaScript draws charts on Canvas   + shows MAE, RMSE, MAPE, PICP numbers


What the UI Looks Like
The left side has your controls, the right side shows results. When you click Run Forecast, it calls the Python backend and draws everything live:

Check if the frontend design skill has useful info

 

Check if the frontend design skill has useful info

 

Let me build a quick working preview of the UI as a React artifact so you can actually see what it looks like:

Created a file, read a file

 

Created a file, read a file

 

☝️ That's a live preview of the UI. Click "Load Demo Data" → "Run Forecast" to see it in action.

Here's the summary:

Tech Stack (Clean)
Layer	Technology	Purpose
Frontend	HTML + CSS + JavaScript	Dark-themed dashboard with Canvas charts
Backend	Python + Flask	REST API serving ML predictions
ML Engine	XGBoost + scikit-learn	Quantile regression (Q10/Q50/Q90) + ensemble
Data Processing	Pandas + NumPy	Cleaning, feature engineering
Visualization	Matplotlib (Python) + Canvas (Browser)	Charts in both notebook & web
Deployment	boto3 + AWS SageMaker	Cloud model serving (optional)
Notebook	Jupyter	Interactive analysis & EDA
API Endpoints
Endpoint	Method	What Happens
/	GET	Serves the web dashboard
/api/status	GET	Returns "ENGINE READY" + model status
/api/forecast	POST	Runs XGBoost ensemble → returns predictions + metrics
/api/train	POST	Retrains models with custom hyperparameters
/api/scenarios	POST	Best-case / Baseline / Worst-case analysis
/api/data/summary	GET	Dataset stats (150K rows, 76 stores, 28 SKUs)
One Command to Run Everything
 

bash

Plain Text


pip install -r requirements.txt && python app.py
Then open http://127.0.0.1:5000 — that's it!

